message.content: AC/DC was incredibly popular in their prime and remains one of the most influential and beloved rock bands of all time. During the 1970s and 1980s, they achieved significant success with albums like "Highway to Hell" (1979) and "Back in Black" (1980), which solidified their status as one of the biggest rock bands in the world. AC/DC's music and high-energy performances resonated with fans, and their unique blend of hard rock and blues made them stand out among their peers. They have sold over 200 million records worldwide and continue to attract new generations of fans with their timeless rock anthems.
